      • SELENIUM_HOST

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_HOST

        Default is set to ""

      • SELENIUM_PORT

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_PORT
        Selenium port, any port where Selenium is running. Used when SELENIUM_RUN_LOCALLY is false
        Default is set to 4444

      • SELENIUM_FIREFOX_PROFILE

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_FIREFOX_PROFILE
        The firefox profile that is to be used for local/remote runs.
        Use this when you would like to have firefox work with your custom firefox profile.
        You can either specify the name of the profile or you can specify the directory location of your firefox profile.
        The framework internally first assumes it to be a profile name. If that assumption fails we fail-over to assuming it to be the firefox profile directory. If that also fails we will work with an anonymous firefox profile.

        WARNING:
        Please be aware that if your firefox profile directory is very huge (above ~10 MB) then there are chances that it can crash your local JVM (be it your desktop or your fusion build job).

      • SELENIUM_SAUCELAB_GRID_CONFIG_FILE

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_SAUCELAB_GRID_CONFIG_FILE
        The name of the JSON file that contains the configuration customization info needed for saucelabs. By default, the configurations specified at Sauce labs Configurations are applicable.

      • SELENIUM_CHROMEDRIVER_PATH

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_CHROMEDRIVER_PATH
        The path to the chromedriver executable on the local machine. This parameter is taken into consideration for local runs involving the Google Chrome browser.

      • SELENIUM_PHANTOMJS_PATH

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_PHANTOMJS_PATH

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_IEDRIVER_PATH

      • SELENIUM_EDGEDRIVER_PATH

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_EDGEDRIVER_PATH
        The path to the EdgeDriver executable on the local machine. This parameter is taken into consideration for local runs involving the Edge browser.

      • SELENIUM_USE_GECKODRIVER

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_USE_GECKODRIVER
        Set this parameter to false to disable the use of Gecko/marionette driver (PKA wires) with Firefox. This is used for local as well as remote grid executions using Firefox browser. Default value is the value of -Dwebdriver.firefox.marionette or true

      • SELENIUM_GECKODRIVER_PATH

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_GECKODRIVER_PATH
        The path to the Gecko/Marionette driver executable file on the local machine. This parameter is taken into consideration for local runs only with the Firefox browser.

      • SELENIUM_USERAGENT

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_USERAGENT
        Use this parameter to set the user agent for firefox when working with Mobile version. This parameter should be set in conjunction with the parameter BROWSER

      • SELENIUM_PROXY_HOST

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_PROXY_HOST
        Use this parameter to set the Proxy server name to be used.

      • SELENIUM_PROXY_PORT

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_PROXY_PORT
        Use this parameter to set the Proxy server port to be used.

      • SELENIUM_USE_SAUCELAB_GRID

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_USE_SAUCELAB_GRID
        Use this parameter to indicate if your remote runs are to be run against the sauce lab grid or against your own grid. This flag is required when running against the Sauce lab grid because we need to disable fetching of the WebDriver node IP and Port details.

      • MOBILE_NODE_TYPE

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty MOBILE_NODE_TYPE
        Use this parameter to execute mobile test cases using respective mobile driver. The valid values are MobileNodeType

      • SELENIUM_CUSTOM_CAPABILITIES_PROVIDER

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_CUSTOM_CAPABILITIES_PROVIDER
        Use this parameter to provide SeLion with a custom capabilities provider. The value for this parameter would be the fully qualified class name which is a sub-class of DefaultCapabilitiesBuilder. If more than one custom capabilities providers are required, please separate their fully qualified class names with commas.

      • SELENIUM_WEBDRIVER_EVENT_LISTENER

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_WEBDRIVER_EVENT_LISTENER
        Use this parameter to provide SeLion with a custom listener which can be plugged into RemoteWebDriver CommandExecutor. If the fully qualified class implements EventListener then SeLion will invoke the custom implementation provided by you as and when the relevant events happen. If more than one custom listeners are required, please separate the fully qualified class names with commas.

      • SELENIUM_RUN_LOCALLY

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty SELENIUM_RUN_LOCALLY
        Flip this parameter to true if you would like a browser to be spawned locally on your machine and run automation tests there. Default is set to false which means your tests are always going to be run against a Remote Grid environment as pointed to by SELENIUM_HOST.

      • MOBILE_APP_FOLDER

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty MOBILE_APP_FOLDER
        This parameter represents the folder which would contain the mobile app. This parameter is currently only useful for local runs. This is the folder from which applications would be searched for by SeLion when it comes to mobile automation in local runs. Please ensure that all the built applications reside in this folder. If no value is provided, SeLion assumes that the application is available under a directory named "Applications" in the current working directory.

      • MOBILE_APP_NAME

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty MOBILE_APP_NAME
        This parameter represents the name of the app that is to be spawned. Specifying the name of the mobile app should suffice. Note: Use of this parameter is not recommended for test suites which test different mobile applications or different versions of the same mobile applications.

      • MOBILE_APP_PATH

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty MOBILE_APP_PATH
        This parameter represents the fully qualified path of the app that is to be spawned. For app exist in the local disk this should be an absolute path, for app exist in the remote location it should be http URL and for app exist in sauce cloud it can be sauce storage like "sauce-storage:testApp.apk".

      • MOBILE_APP_LANGUAGE

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty MOBILE_APP_LANGUAGE
        This parameter represents the language to be used. By default it is always English represented as en

      • MOBILE_APP_LOCALE

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty MOBILE_APP_LOCALE
        This parameter represents the locale to be used. By default it is always US English represented as en_US

      • MOBILE_DRIVER_SESSION_TIMEOUT

        public static final Config.ConfigProperty MOBILE_DRIVER_SESSION_TIMEOUT
        Maximum duration of a session duration in milliseconds. Session will be forcefully terminated if it takes longer.
        The value of this parameter is used as the value of sessionTimeout for ios-driver and selendroid.
        This configuration affects LOCAL EXECUTION RUNS only i.e., when SELENIUM_RUN_LOCALLY is set to true.
        The unit is milliseconds.
        Default is set to 1800000 milliseconds.
